Oluwabamikemi Kayode is a versatile professional and community builder, serving as a community manager, Python developer, technical writer, open-source advocate, event organizer, and tech host.

She leads community marketing at the AsyncAPI Initiative (focused on event-driven architectures) and consults with OSPO Now to help sustain the DSWB community. Previously, she managed community programs at Tunga.
She is passionate about empowering the next generation, especially women in tech. She champions community-driven growth and shares insights on her blog about technology, community building, open source, and personal growth.
She contributes to SheCodeAfrica (Technical Coordinator), Layer5, Open Source Community Africa, Google Developers Group Lagos, CHAOSS, and Web3Afrika.
When she is not building communities, she is organizing, hosting, or speaking at events such as API Conference Lagos, Open Source Community Festival, Community Manager Festival, and GDG events
